By ‚Ä¢ @curlykidlife How filmmakers milk a cow ü•õüêÑ üìΩ

___

HOW I MADE IT?

1. At first I thought I could film it all as one shot. However it proved difficult as the cow needed to stay in position from start to finish. 
2. The solution I came up with was to make a stand in rig for the cows udders, which could be replaced in post production with a real cow back plate.
3. I filmed the cow in position first which then allowed me to position makeshift udders in place of the real udders for the 2nd shot.
4. I used a blue screen for keying my body and green card for the udders.

How did you think it was made?
